question:
Let $n, m, k$ be positive integers. Let $ ar{\mu} = (\mu_1, \dots, \mu_m)$ and $ ar{
u} = (
u_1, \dots, 
u_k)$ be tuples of positive integers. Let $\mathcal{P}_{n}^c( ar{\mu}, ar{
u})$ be the set of all complex polynomials $p(z)=\prod_{i=1}^{m}(z-z_i)^{\mu_i}$, where $\sum_{i=1}^m\mu_i=n$, whose derivatives have the form $p'(z)=n\prod_{i=1}^{m}(z-z_i)^{\mu_i-1}\prod_{j=1}^{k}(z-\xi_j)^{
u_j}$, with $\sum_{j=1}^k
u_j=m-1$. A result on the analyticity domains of critical points establishes that, for a fixed ordering, the distinct zeros $\{z_i\}_{i=1}^m$ and the distinct critical points $\{\xi_j\}_{j=1}^k$ of polynomials in $\mathcal{P}_{n}^c( ar{\mu}, ar{
u})$ can be locally expressed as analytic functions of any subset of exactly $d$ variables chosen from $\{z_1, \dots, z_m\}$. What is the value of $d$ as a function of the parameters $n, m,$ and/or $k$?
